This diagram illustrates how RAR works in a real banking context. It covers the full lifecycle of a wire transfer authorization — from the moment the user initiates the transaction in the SPA, through the consent screen generated by the Authorization Server, the policy decisions made by the PDP, the technical checks performed by the API Gateway, the RAR binding verification done by the microservice, and finally the instruction sent to the SAB Core Banking system. Each component has a clearly defined responsibility and none of them trusts the previous one blindly.

sequenceDiagram
participant SPA as SPA (Public Client)
participant AS as Authorization Server
participant PDP as PDP Component (OPA)
participant U as User Browser
participant GW as API Gateway
participant MS as Microservice (Wire Transfer)
participant RS as Resource Server (Core Banking)

Note over SPA,AS: Phase 1 - Authorization Request with RAR

SPA->>AS: GET /authorize?response_type=code<br/>&authorization_details=[{type:wire_transfer,<br/>amount:47500, creditorIBAN:FR76...}]<br/>&code_challenge=S256&scope=openid+wire_transfer

Note over AS: Parse authorization_details
Note over AS: Select policy and consent template

AS->>PDP: Evaluate authorization request
Note over PDP: Is this request type allowed ?
Note over PDP: Is the amount within allowed range ?
Note over PDP: Is the creditor IBAN on a fraud watchlist ?
Note over PDP: Is the debtor account owned by this client ?

PDP-->>AS: decision: allow + enriched context<br/>(consent details, required SCA level)

AS-->>U: Consent screen<br/>"Authorize EUR 47,500.00 to ACME Corp SAS<br/>(FR7630006000011234567890189) ?"

U->>AS: Authenticate + confirm

Note over AS: Phase 2 - Token Issuance

AS-->>SPA: 302 redirect ?code=AUTH_CODE

SPA->>AS: POST /token<br/>(code + code_verifier)

AS-->>SPA: access_token {<br/>  sub: user123,<br/>  scope: wire_transfer,<br/>  authorization_details: [{<br/>    type: wire_transfer,<br/>    amount: 47500.00,<br/>    creditorIBAN: FR76...,<br/>    debtorIBAN: FR76...<br/>  }]<br/>}

Note over SPA,RS: Phase 3 - API Call and Policy Enforcement

SPA->>GW: POST /transfers<br/>(Bearer token + transaction body)

Note over GW: Check 1 - JWT signature valid ?
Note over GW: Check 2 - Token not expired ?
Note over GW: Check 3 - Audience matches this service ?
Note over GW: Check 4 - Scope wire_transfer present ?

GW-->>SPA: 401 if any technical check fails

GW->>MS: Forward request (token + body)

Note over MS: Re-validate JWT independently
Note over MS: RAR binding check
Note over MS: token.amount == body.amount ?
Note over MS: token.creditorIBAN == body.creditorIBAN ?

MS-->>SPA: 403 if binding check fails

MS->>PDP: POST /v1/data/banking/transfers<br/>{<br/>  token_claims: authorization_details,<br/>  request_body: {amount, creditorIBAN, debtorIBAN},<br/>  user_profile: {daily_limit, approval_level}<br/>}

Note over PDP: Policy 1 - Amount within daily limit ?
Note over PDP: Policy 2 - Dual approval required ?
Note over PDP: Policy 3 - Creditor IBAN not flagged ?
Note over PDP: Policy 4 - User authorized to debit this account ?

PDP-->>MS: decision: allow / deny + reason

MS-->>SPA: 403 + reason if PDP denies

MS->>RS: Initiate transfer (all checks passed)
RS-->>MS: Transfer confirmed
MS-->>SPA: 200 Transfer initiated
